Data from the Office for National Statistics show the number of payroll jobs held by EU nationals fell by six percent in the two years to 2021, but that of non-EU nationals increased by nine percent. The increase in non-EU workers is reported to have been driven by the health sector. The fall in the number of EU workers in Britain is, however, understood to have been caused in large part by the Covid pandemic, despite claims Brexit would drive foreign workers out of the country. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...